properties.Text: Remember this guy? He did so well last time that I promoted him to Senior Button Driver.
I think there's a toilet overflowing somewhere.
This was not part of the plan. Go around, I suppose.
I called a plumber. I'm sure he'll know.

You like it?
I call it, "The Don Quixote".

Let's talke a stroll around and then we'll come back at the end.

I just got off the phone with the plumber. He says, and I quote, "The water is by design. I'm marking your service ticket 'closed'."

What a real piece of you-know-what.

No big deal, right? Let's offer it up and move on.
Okay, we're coming up to our first stop.

Funny story about this guy. One night I was out at a club and I saw him in the parking lot, and I was all like, "Hey, want a job?".
And he said, "Sure, whatever."

That's actually the whole story. I can't remember why it was funny.

You're going to laugh, but I just remembered that I told the plumbers to flood this room a week ago because I was trying to get a huge insurance claim.\n\nCapitalism, am I right? What are you gonna do...
And we're back at the main attraction: The Don Quixote.\n\nSee you in the next room.
You are legally an absolute hardass.

Without admitting fault, I hereby publicly acknowledge the unfortunate deaths of people who used the above corridor. 

I further wish to celebrate the opening of this new auxiliary tunnel (on the right) so that further unfortunate tragedy may be avoided.
LEGAL NOTICE 2 OF 3\n\nHaving said that, those who still wish to participate in the above path, which is totally rad, may push the brown button.
